      • toMultimap

        public static <K,V> com.google.common.collect.Multimap<K,V> toMultimap(java.lang.Iterable<? extends V> values,
                                                                       org.eclipse.xtext.xbase.lib.Functions.Function1<? super V,K> computeKeys)
        Returns a multimap where each key is the result of invoking the supplied function computeKeys on its corresponding value. If the function produces the same key for different values, multiple values will be available for that particular key.
        Parameters:
        values - the values to use when constructing the Multimap. Must not be null.
        computeKeys - the function used to produce the key for each value. Must not be null.

      • toPrettyString

        public static java.lang.String toPrettyString(java.lang.Iterable<?> any,
                                              java.lang.String andOrNor)
        Returns with the string representation of the iterable argument after calling the Object.toString() method on each elements. The elements are separated by a comma (,) while the very last element is with the andOrNor argument.
